registration: Registration is $10 for riders. Registration and payment can be made at the track or a season pass can be purchased up until June 1st.

title: Allegheny Cycling Assocation Saturday Morning Crit
description: Allegheny Cycling Association Saturday Morning Criterium Series. Races will be run for all classes of racers with no mixing of classes.
course: Course is a 1/2 mile paved oval located at Pittsburgh\'s Bud Harris Cycling Track. Course subject to change week to week.  (It is not going to be just laps normal laps around the oval every week).  We have some great course design we will we throwing at you.
registration:
Preregister: By purchasing a ABRA Oval Season Pass your are are guaranteed entry into every race, since buying a season pass implies pre-registration. With field limits of 35 rider per field this is very important if you want to insure a starting spot. There will be bikereg pages offered to Preregister for separate ABRA Oval Series events (at $17 per online entry) however by purchasing the ABRA season pass you save $2 per race and only get charged Bikereg.com service fee once!
Second Race Entered only $10.00
(Season Pass only good for one race per day)

Race day registration will be $20 and will open at 8:00AM (please see field limit and guaranteed racing spot information below. USAC License required for all riders.  Annual License or One-day Licenses can be purchased at the event for those who do not hold a USAC Racing License.
notes:
2012 Oval Racing Series Rules:
To qualify for series championship you must complete 8 of the 10 events.

Final race worth DOUBLE POINTS

Total points will be determined by your best 8 races.

Points to be given by finishing order at each event to top 15 finishers per event.

No points will be given for DNS or DNF.

In case of ties, Finishing order at final race is tie breaker. 

To race in the ABRA Oval Series you must hold a USAC License or purchase a one day license at each event.
ABRA Oval Series follows guidelines set for by USAC rule book.

Note that August 4th race is NOT included in the ABRA series. This is a separate race managed by the ACA outside of ABRA rules and rega.

West Chester Cross Classic
description: First annual West Chester Cross Classic is brought to you by Chester County Velo and Rustin High School wrestling team.  Held on the beautiful Bayard Rustin High School campus, this race promises to be a classic on the Philadelphia cross scene.
course: Classic cyclocross course with two sets of barriers and variable terrain mostly grass, with some pavement. The 1.9 mile closed course is great for spectators. Course will be flowing and challenging, making use of natural run-ups, off cambers sections, and lots of cornering. Course is designed by angry Bob Reuther, local cross legend and long time advocate of local cycling.
registration:
Pre-registration will be open on bikereg.com until October 18, 2012 11:00PM.
         There is a $5 late fee for day-of registration.
         Day of Registration and sign-in will be open at 8AM and will close 30 min prior to each race.
         A USAC license is required to participate in this race, day-of and annual licenses will be available for purchase at registration.
         Additional races are $10
         Registration price includes $3 USAC insurance fee.
notes: In order to promote local cross racing, we have limited all entry fees to $20 or less (except Pro 1/2/3 field).  In addition,this race serves as a fund raiser for Rustin HS Wrestling Team, and a $5 per car parking fee will be collected 100% of which will go to the team (car pooling is encouraged!  Fans and spectators are can park for free).
directions:
Bayard Rustin High School
1100 Shiloh Road
West Chester, PA 19382
